# Story scroll effect (KEEP — user approved)

The **home-story** scrollytelling section is the preferred audience/intro pattern for this site. Do not replace or regress it without explicit user request.

## What to preserve

- **Pinned scroll track**: `height: calc(var(--story-beats) * 100vh)` on `.home-story-track`
- **Sticky viewport**: `.home-story` sticks at `top: var(--nav-h)` while the user scrolls through beats
- **Sticky left video**: portrait reel with rounded corners; do not remove or shrink without reason
- **Dashed rail + moving dot**: `.home-story__rail`, dashed `.home-story__line`, `.home-story__dot` driven by `dotProgress`
- **One slide at a time**: only `.home-story__slide--active` visible on desktop; crossfade between beats
- **Single page scroll**: no nested scroll containers inside the section
- **Large display typography**: `.home-story__copy` / `.home-story__item` use `font-display`, ~`clamp(1.45rem, 2.65vw, 2.15rem)`

## Implementation map

| Piece | Location |
|-------|----------|
| Beats + markup | `pages/index.js` → `STORY_BEATS`, `.home-story-*` |
| Scroll logic | `pages/index.js` → `useStoryScroll` (inline) |
| Hero scroll logic | `pages/index.js` → `useScrollHeroTransition` (inline) |
| Styles | `styles/globals.css` → `.home-story-*` block |

## Beat sequence (reference)

1. Welcome intro (brand bold + inline links)
2. Situations lead-in
3. Numbered situations 1–3
4. Closing CTA with link
5. Brand personality line

## Static / mobile

Below 901px or `prefers-reduced-motion`: `.home-story-track--static` — all beats stacked, no pin, no slide swap.

## When extending

- Add beats → update `STORY_BEATS`, `--story-beats` auto from length, keep one-viewport-per-beat scroll distance
- Do not reintroduce dual scroll (fixed panel + `overflow-y: auto`)
- Landing-page-only logic stays in `pages/index.js` until a second page needs it
